Mrs Babcock, Palmer's sister claimed he rushed to her house straight after the killing and admitted what he'd done.

'He just came in and said, 'Here’s money to pay my taxes with, I’ve had enough.

'I
shot and killed Tammy. Give me an hour to get away and then do whatever
you have to do — call the police... whatever you have to do,' and then 
he just took off,' Babcock told CBS.

Ms Babcock said she immediately called police, who believe he fled into Harriman State Park, which backs onto his property.

Search teams began hunting woods 
for the man, a retired park ranger, using tracking dogs and helicopters. They soon discovered his vehicle, a 1995 green Dodge Ram 
pickup truck.

Tammy Palmer's parents are struggling to come to terms with the loss of their daughter. They say her relationship with her father-in-law had grown increasingly ugly, culminating in a fight.

'She
told me 'Mommy, don’t worry I’ll be alright.' I don’t think she ever 
thought that this man would kill her,' Tammy's mother Violet Pannirello 
told CBS.

