Palmer's criminal past and warned that he is believed to be dangerous - 
owning to a large gun collection.

It has been reported by police that the grandfather had previously threatened to kill a Department of Environmental Conservation officer.

He was arrested and charged 
with second-degree aggravated harassment after he made repeated 'life 
threatening' calls to Department of Environmental Conservation employee Kenneth Didion’s home over a period 
of months starting in December 1984, The Journal News reported.

Palmer, working as a truck driver at 
the time, pleaded guilty in April 1986 and the next month was sentenced 
to one year probation and fined $750. He also was ordered to avoid any 
contact with Didion for a year.

